history.content:
I personally wouldn't want to be taking 184 and 162 concurrently; double projects are going to be a pretty rough time. That being said, if you have a stellar group for 162 and you happen to be REALLY good at managing your time (or you don't care about sleep/having a life at all), it could be doable.

---

In my experience, 194-26 was more work than 184. There were 9 projects when I took 194-26, and only 4 when I took 184, though admittedly the 184 projects were maybe 1.5x longer. I don't know how much work 162 entails, but I took 161, 170, 184, and 188 in the same semester with no issues, to give you a point of reference.

I personally wouldn't want to be taking 184 and 162 concurrently; double projects are going to be a pretty rough time. That being said, if you have a stellar group for 162 and you happen to be REALLY good at managing your time (or you don't care about sleep/having a life at all), it could be doable.
It seems like 194-26 is full, so I might just add 184 instead. I've heard 184 is a lot more work compared to 194-26. Is it going to be too much together with 161 and 162?
history.subject: 161, 162, 184 too much?
